==Turkish==
===Etymology===
From {{der|tr|otk|yara-||to suit, fit, to be beneficial}}, from {{inh|tr|trk-pro|*yara-||to be beneficial, useful, successful}}<ref>{{R:tut-pro:SDM}}: [http://starling.rinet.ru/cgi-bin/response.cgi?single=1&basename=%2fdata%2falt%2faltet&text_number=2581&root=config “*ǯắra”]</ref>. Cognate with {{cog|ba|ярау}}, {{cog|tt|ярарга}}, {{cog|uz|yaramoq}}.
===Verb===
{{tr-verb|yarar}}
# {{lb|tr|intransitive}} to [[benefit]], [[serve]] (someone's) purpose; to serve, [[avail]]; to be good for
#: {{ux|tr|''Savaş kimseye '''yaramaz'''.''|War '''does not serve''' anyone.|inline=1}}
